{"key":"post-10728010","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10728010</id>\n<content>We've had at least three 'should I sterilize the verm' threads this week, and at least three lighting threads.&amp;nbsp; Does nobody even read the forum any more to learn from other people's threads? &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/shrug.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:shrug:&quot; title=&quot;:shrug:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Yes, you should heat treat the verm.&amp;nbsp; Contrary to incorrect info posted above, verm IS nutritious and will support molds.&amp;nbsp; If it's factory sealed in the bag, you can get away with using it as-is, but if the bag has been opened for awhile, it could have mold spores lurking on the contents.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bright light from a window or fluorescent is superior to dim light.&amp;nbsp; They don't just need light to pin.&amp;nbsp; Mushrooms derive energy from the light and will grow thicker and heavier with better developed caps if exposed to bright light on a normal day/night schedule.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>10727858</prev>\n<first>10726981</first>\n<last>10728010</last>\n<when>1248388545</when>\n<utime>07/24/09 01:35 AM</utime>\n</post>"}